cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper primarily focuses on the multimedia service paradigm and the challenges faced by non-professional broadcasters in live streaming platforms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the architecture and access data of Twitch.tv, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The study also explores the impact of delay on viewers' interactive experience, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges faced by broadcasters in terms of dynamic uploading capacity, which falls under the category of cs.SD (Software Engineering).
